race.comment: MOEGREEN (7) lifted strongly to score by 1.5 lengths three runs back at Townsville before filling a minor placing at his last two starts. Has a great record at this journey with three wins from seven starts and is sure to run well. SPIRIT MEISTER (4) went forward and proved too strong last time out, scoring by 2 lengths over 1250m at this track. Drawn to enjoy a good run on the speed. Has his share of talent and is hard to beat in this suitable race. BURRANEER BUOY (6) was successful last start over 1400m at Townsville, getting home by half a length to make it three wins in a row. Well placed and there is no reason why he cannot score again. TYCOON BEAU (2) showed little early speed then came with a powerful run to finish third last time out over 1250m here. Has a win and two minor placings at this journey from four starts and is one of the better hopes.
